\title{"screenshot"}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Use when the user explicitly asks for a desktop or system screenshot (full screen, specific app or window, or a pixel region), or when tool-specific capture capabilities are unavailable and an OS-level capture is needed."}

\subtree{
\title{Screenshot Capture}
\p{Follow these save-location rules every time:}

\ol{
\li{If the user specifies a path, save there.}
\li{If the user asks for a screenshot without a path, save to the OS default screenshot location.}
\li{If Codex needs a screenshot for its own inspection, save to the temp directory.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tool priority}
\ul{
\li{Prefer tool-specific screenshot capabilities when available (for example: a Figma MCP/skill for Figma files, or Playwright/agent-browser tools for browsers and Electron apps).}
\li{Use this skill when explicitly asked, for whole-system desktop captures, or when a tool-specific capture cannot get what you need.}
\li{Otherwise, treat this skill as the default for desktop apps without a better-integrated capture tool.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{macOS permission preflight (reduce repeated prompts)}
\p{On macOS, run the preflight helper once before window/app capture. It checks Screen Recording permission, explains why it is needed, and requests it in one place.}

\p{The helpers route Swift's module cache to \code{\startverb $TMPDIR/codex-swift-module-cache\stopverb} to avoid extra sandbox module-cache prompts.}

\pre{\startverb
bash <path-to-skill>/scripts/ensure_macos_permissions.sh
\stopverb}

\p{To avoid multiple sandbox approval prompts, combine preflight + capture in one command when possible:}

\pre{\startverb
bash <path-to-skill>/scripts/ensure_macos_permissions.sh && \
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --app "Codex"
\stopverb}

\p{For Codex inspection runs, keep the output in temp:}

\pre{\startverb
bash <path-to-skill>/scripts/ensure_macos_permissions.sh && \
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --app "<App>" --mode temp
\stopverb}

\p{Use the bundled scripts to avoid re-deriving OS-specific commands.}
}

\subtree{
\title{macOS and Linux (Python helper)}
\p{Run the helper from the repo root:}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py
\stopverb}

\p{Common patterns:}

\ul{
\li{Default location (user asked for "a screenshot"):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Temp location (Codex visual check):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --mode temp
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Explicit location (user provided a path or filename):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --path output/screen.png
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{App/window capture by app name (macOS only; substring match is OK; captures all matching windows):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --app "Codex"
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Specific window title within an app (macOS only):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --app "Codex" --window-name "Settings"
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{List matching window ids before capturing (macOS only):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --list-windows --app "Codex"
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Pixel region (x,y,w,h):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --mode temp --region 100,200,800,600
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Focused/active window (captures only the frontmost window; use \code{\startverb --app\stopverb} to capture all windows):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --mode temp --active-window
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Specific window id (use --list-windows on macOS to discover ids):}
}

\pre{\startverb
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --window-id 12345
\stopverb}

\p{The script prints one path per capture. When multiple windows or displays match, it prints multiple paths (one per line) and adds suffixes like \code{\startverb -w<windowId>\stopverb} or \code{\startverb -d<display>\stopverb}. View each path sequentially with the image viewer tool, and only manipulate images if needed or requested.}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow examples}
\ul{
\li{"Take a look at <App> and tell me what you see": capture to temp, then view each printed path in order.}
}

\pre{\startverb
bash <path-to-skill>/scripts/ensure_macos_permissions.sh && \
python3 <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.py --app "<App>" --mode temp
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{"The design from Figma is not matching what is implemented": use a Figma MCP/skill to capture the design first, then capture the running app with this skill (typically to temp) and compare the raw screenshots before any manipulation.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Multi-display behavior}
\ul{
\li{On macOS, full-screen captures save one file per display when multiple monitors are connected.}
\li{On Linux and Windows, full-screen captures use the virtual desktop (all monitors in one image); use \code{\startverb --region\stopverb} to isolate a single display when needed.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Linux prerequisites and selection logic}
\p{The helper automatically selects the first available tool:}

\ol{
\li{\code{\startverb scrot\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb gnome-screenshot\stopverb}}
\li{ImageMagick \code{\startverb import\stopverb}}
}

\p{If none are available, ask the user to install one of them and retry.}

\p{Coordinate regions require \code{\startverb scrot\stopverb} or ImageMagick \code{\startverb import\stopverb}.}

\p{\code{\startverb --app\stopverb}, \code{\startverb --window-name\stopverb}, and \code{\startverb --list-windows\stopverb} are macOS-only. On Linux, use \code{\startverb --active-window\stopverb} or provide \code{\startverb --window-id\stopverb} when available.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Windows (PowerShell helper)}
\p{Run the PowerShell helper:}

\pre{\startverb
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.ps1
\stopverb}

\p{Common patterns:}

\ul{
\li{Default location:}
}

\pre{\startverb
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.ps1
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Temp location (Codex visual check):}
}

\pre{\startverb
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.ps1 -Mode temp
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Explicit path:}
}

\pre{\startverb
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.ps1 -Path "C:\Temp\screen.png"
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Pixel region (x,y,w,h):}
}

\pre{\startverb
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.ps1 -Mode temp -Region 100,200,800,600
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Active window (ask the user to focus it first):}
}

\pre{\startverb
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.ps1 -Mode temp -ActiveWindow
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Specific window handle (only when provided):}
}

\pre{\startverb
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File <path-to-skill>/scripts/take_screenshot.ps1 -WindowHandle 123456
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Direct OS commands (fallbacks)}
\p{Use these when you cannot run the helpers.}

\subtree{
\title{macOS}
\ul{
\li{Full screen to a specific path:}
}

\pre{\startverb
screencapture -x output/screen.png
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Pixel region:}
}

\pre{\startverb
screencapture -x -R100,200,800,600 output/region.png
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Specific window id:}
}

\pre{\startverb
screencapture -x -l12345 output/window.png
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Interactive selection or window pick:}
}

\pre{\startverb
screencapture -x -i output/interactive.png
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Linux}
\ul{
\li{Full screen:}
}

\pre{\startverb
scrot output/screen.png
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
gnome-screenshot -f output/screen.png
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
import -window root output/screen.png
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Pixel region:}
}

\pre{\startverb
scrot -a 100,200,800,600 output/region.png
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
import -window root -crop 800x600+100+200 output/region.png
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Active window:}
}

\pre{\startverb
scrot -u output/window.png
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
gnome-screenshot -w -f output/window.png
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Error handling}
\ul{
\li{On macOS, run \code{\startverb bash <path-to-skill>/scripts/ensure_macos_permissions.sh\stopverb} first to request Screen Recording in one place.}
\li{If you see "screen capture checks are blocked in the sandbox", "could not create image from display", or Swift \code{\startverb ModuleCache\stopverb} permission errors in a sandboxed run, rerun the command with escalated permissions.}
\li{If macOS app/window capture returns no matches, run \code{\startverb --list-windows --app "AppName"\stopverb} and retry with \code{\startverb --window-id\stopverb}, and make sure the app is visible on screen.}
\li{If Linux region/window capture fails, check tool availability with \code{\startverb command -v scrot\stopverb}, \code{\startverb command -v gnome-screenshot\stopverb}, and \code{\startverb command -v import\stopverb}.}
\li{If saving to the OS default location fails with permission errors in a sandbox, rerun the command with escalated permissions.}
\li{Always report the saved file path in the response.}
}
}
}